<HEAD>Thunderstorms Dampen Midwest, South</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms drenched much of the nation today, while snow fell
in Minnesota and Colorado.
   Showers and thunderstorms this morning extended from
northeastern Texas and southeastern Oklahoma across much of
Arkansas. Thunderstorms also extended from east-central Missouri to
southern Ohio and northern West Virginia.
   Elsewhere, scattered showers and thunderstorms also dampened
Mississippi, Alabama, Georgia and South Carolina, while light rain
fell on the upper Mississippi Valley and the central Plains.
   Snow was falling over Duluth, Minn., and Trinidad, Colo.
   Heavier rainfall for the six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT included
1{ inches in Cincinnati and nearly an inch in Belleville, Ill., and
Columbus, Ohio.
   On Friday, a severe thunderstorm in west-central Indiana spawned
a tornado at Oaktown. Thunderstorms also produced more than 2
inches of rain in Fairfield, Ohio, and dropped baseball size-hail
on Arlington, Texas, and golf ball-size hail at Valley Station, Ky.
Strong thunderstorm winds downed power lines around Grady, Ark.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
from southeast Texas across the Gulf Coast and over the Tennessee
and Ohio valleys to the middle and south Atlantic Coast; rain
showers from Iowa across the Great Lakes region to New York and New
Jersey; and a mixture of rain and snow from Minnesota across the
northern Plains to the northern and central Rockies.
   Highs were expected to be in the 40s and 50s over most of New
England and from the northern and central Rockies across the
northern half of the Great Plains and the upper Mississippi Valley
to Michigan; in the 80s from California to southern New Mexico and
from Texas across the Gulf Coast and Tennessee Valley to the
southern Atlantic Coast; in the 90s in Florida and the desert
Southwest; and in the 60s and 70s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 18
degrees at Yellowstone Park in Wyoming to 79 degrees at Key West,
Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 71 cloudy; Boston 42 partly cloudy; Buffalo 44
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 72 foggy; Cincinnati 60 thunderstorms;
Cleveland 49 partly cloudy; Detroit 45 cloudy; Miami 75 fair; New
York 51 partly cloudy; Philadelphia 54 cloudy; Pittsburgh 50
cloudy; Portland, Maine 33 fair; Washington 56 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 43 partly cloudy; Chicago 51 foggy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 66 fair; Denver 34 snow; Des Moines 48 fair;
Indianapolis 62 foggy; Kansas City 54 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 41
rain; Nashville 66 cloudy; New Orleans 71 cloudy; St. Louis 64
thunderstorms.
   _West: Albuquerque 50 fair; Anchorage 44 fair; Las Vegas 63
fair; Los Angeles 59 fair; Phoenix 68 fair; Salt Lake City 41 fair;
San Diego 60 fair; San Francisco 54 fair; Seattle 53 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 37 fair; Toronto 43 cloudy.
