<FIRST>r i PM-Malaysia-MineCollapse     04-29 0124</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Malaysia-Mine Collapse,0126</SECOND>
<HEAD>Boy Rescued From Collapsed Mine, 12 Remain Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Workers today rescued a boy from
the rubble of a collapsed gold mine in northeastern Malaysia and
searched for 12 other prospectors believed trapped, authorities
said.
   The rescue workers found one body as they searched for gold
diggers buried in Friday's collapse in Bukit Lubuk Mandi, 180 miles
northeast of Kuala Lumpur.
   It was not immediately known what caused the shafts to give way,
a police spokesman said on condition of anonymity.
   Shekh Hamdan Shekh Awi, 17, was rescued and rushed to a
hospital, the national news agency Bernama reported. His condition
was not immediately known. The report identified the fatality as
Syed Ahmad Engku Embong, 31.
