<HEAD>Police Seize 29 Pounds of Cocaine and Heroin In Milan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILAN, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police stopped a car on a highway near Milan
on Saturday, seized $10 million worth of cocaine and heroin, and
arrested the driver, authorities said.
   Investigators said the drugs, 22 pounds of cocaine and seven
pounds of heroin, probably were intended for distribution in
southern Italy by the Camorra, an underworld organization in Naples.
   Milan police, who had the driver under surveillance, said they
followed the car 20 miles before they stopped it on the
Milan-Bologna highway at a point where the exits were controlled to
prevent escape.
   The driver, 37-year-old Antonio Arena of Naples, was arrested
and charged with drug trafficking, police said.
