<HEAD>Estranged Wife Says She Watched Husband Commit Two Murders</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 6th graf, `Swan said ...,' to restore first reference to
Swan.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The estranged wife of a man arrested in
connection with four stabbing deaths told police she watched her
husband commit two of the slayings, officials said.
   Ricky Lee Green, 28, of Azle was being held Saturday on $1.25
million bail on charges of murder and capital murder in the
slayings, which occurred in 1985 and 1986. Officers arrested Green
at his home Thursday morning after obtaining a statement from
Sharon Green.
   Wise County Sheriff Leroy Burch said Mrs. Green told police that
in both of the slayings she allegedly witnessed, her husband
brought a woman home, attacked her with a hammer and sexually
assaulted her in the bathroom.
   Mrs. Green said her husband would then call her into the room
and tell her to watch while he stabbed the woman repeatedly, Burch
said.
   Police said Green has confessed to the four slayings, but he
said that his wife helped him kill the two women; Mrs. Green
maintains she only watched the slayings, Burch said.
   Police Lt. Tommy Swan said Mrs. Green, 28, is not a suspect ``at
this time'' in any of the slayings. Green had been considered a
suspect in one of the slayings for some time, police said.
   The victims were a television advertising executive, a
16-year-old boy, a 27-year old Fort Worth woman and an unidentified
woman, police said.
   Mrs. Green told police she had kept her husband's secrets for
several years because she was afraid of him, Fort Worth Detective
Roger SoRelle said.
   Tarrant County Jail officials were monitoring Green's cell and
activities closely after he tried to hang himself with a T-shirt
Thursday night.
   Swan identified the victims as Steven Fefferman, 28, an
advertising executive from KXAS-TV; Jeffrey L. Davis, 16, of Fort
Worth; Sandra Lorraine Bailey, 27, of Fort Worth; and a woman
identified only as ``Betty Jo.''
   The two males died of multiple stab wounds, police said.
