   West German officials say NATO nations
are starting to line up against the U.S. and British views in a
major disarmament dispute within the Western alliance.
   Chancellor Helmut Kohl's call for superpower negotiations on
short-range nuclear weapons has placed him in a battle of wills
against both President Bush and British Prime Minister Margaret
Thatcher.
   Mrs. Thatcher and Kohl are scheduled to meet Sunday in West
Germany to discuss the issue.
   Foreign Minister Hans-Dietrich Genscher spent part of Friday
talking about the dispute, one of the most divisive in recent years
